         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               <choice corresp="#a1">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">Like (the shoemaker) from the leather [11a] <hi>Sanskrit</hi> (is) cutting out (material) for a sandal [11b],</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a2">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">As many of the desires one renounces [11c], <hi>Sanskrit</hi> as much (happiness is established).</seg></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">Was immer man an Begierden aufgibt, das eben (wird [einem] als Glück zuteil).</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Whichever desires one gives up, exactly this (is bestowed [on one] as a blessing).</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>418</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a3">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl"><hi>Sanskrit</hi> If one longs for complete happiness [12a], <hi>Sanskrit</hi></seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a3 #a4">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">Wenn man das ganze Glück sucht, soll man alle Begierden aufheben. [Nur] wer alle Begierden aufgibt, erreicht das höchste Glück.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">If one is seeking entire bliss, one should revoke all desires. [Only] he who abandons all desires, will reach the highest bliss.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>150</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a4">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">one should completely renounce all desires [12b]. <hi>Sanskrit</hi> The one renouncing all desires completely, [12c] <hi>Sanskrit</hi></seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b1">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">[12d] <hi>Sanskrit</hi> Because one is running after desires, [13a] <hi>Sanskrit</hi></seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b2">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">one has not obtained satisfaction of the mind. [13b] <hi>Sanskrit</hi> There(fore) ... [13c]</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b3">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl"><hi>Sanskrit</hi> Those (are) satisfied indeed (who are well-satisfied) through wisdom. [13d]</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b4">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl"><hi>Sanskrit</hi> Excellent (is) the satisfaction through wisdom. [14a] <hi>Sanskrit</hi></seg></seg>
               </choice>
            </p>
