&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a4.&lt;/b&gt; The verbal form ending with &lt;i&gt;-tär&lt;/i&gt; ought to be restored as &lt;i&gt;riñiträ&lt;/i&gt;. The translation of the pāda 12b Skt. &lt;i&gt;sarvakāmāṃ parityajet&lt;/i&gt; was certainly &lt;i&gt;po yśelmeṃ päst riñiträ&lt;/i&gt;. The correct Sanskrit form should be &lt;i&gt;sarvakāmaparityāgī&lt;/i&gt; (12c). &lt;i&gt;sukha&lt;/i&gt; at the end of the line is the beginning of Skt. &lt;i&gt;sukham edhate&lt;/i&gt; (12d).
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b1.&lt;/b&gt; Note that the Sanskrit text has the reading &lt;i&gt;anusaraṃ&lt;/i&gt; in all manuscripts. The spelling &lt;i&gt;-an&lt;sub&gt;\&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/i&gt; is consistent with the spelling &lt;i&gt;-am&lt;sub&gt;\&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/i&gt; met in other instances in this same manuscript. At the end of the line &lt;i&gt;na&lt;/i&gt; is the first word of the pāda 13a. Very tentatively one can interpret the remains of the akṣaras at the beginning of the line as reflecting a 3.sg.mid. verbal form matching Skt. &lt;i&gt;edhate&lt;/i&gt; (12d), possibly &lt;i&gt;(yän)[m](ās)[tä]r&lt;/i&gt; ‘he obtains’.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b2.&lt;/b&gt; At the end of the line &lt;i&gt;tu&lt;/i&gt; ought to be completed to &lt;i&gt;tumeṃ&lt;/i&gt; matching Skt. &lt;i&gt;tataḥ&lt;/i&gt; at the beginning of pāda 13c.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b3.&lt;/b&gt; At the end of the line one should restore the perlative singular &lt;i&gt;aiśamñesa&lt;/i&gt; translating Skt. &lt;i&gt;prajñayā&lt;/i&gt; (13d).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b4.&lt;/b&gt; The complete Sanskrit pāda 14b is: &lt;i&gt;na hi kāmair vitṛpyate&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</item>
